name: PageDetail
desc: The number of items that return in the page.

items.name: itemsPerPage
items.desc: The maximum number of entries that return for this operation, which is the value of count in the GET operation. The actual number of entries that return can be less than the maximum itemsPerPage.

items.name: startIndex
items.desc: The offset of the first entry that returns. Use offset in the request query string or Selector to override the default value of 0. For example, if the request is offset=5, the response startIndex is also 5. A value of 0 retrieves the first itemsPerPage results from the full result set.

items.name: totalResults
items.desc: The total number of entries that return for the operation.
